@Gibitop packages are often highly interdependent internally (see the [bsky post](https://bsky.app/profile/haz.dev/post/3lckcvhdn2s2a)) and in practice separate packages causes nightmarish bugs: https://github.com/radix-ui/primitives/issues/1088. Radix went the other way to a monopackage specifically due to these types of issues with version mismatches.

> This means we have to thoroughly test every component in our quite large application to see if updating the caused anything else to break / not work as we expected prior to the update.

That's certainly one appeal of separate packages, but often they have shared dependencies (e.g. many low-level utils) that are updated anyway when you upgrade one of the packages, which ends up affecting the other component packages indirectly even though they weren't upgraded explicitly since the version gets bumped
